**1. How high would you have to count before you would use the letter "A" in the English language spelling of a whole number?**

You'd have to count to **one hundred and one** (101) before you use the letter "A" in the English spelling of a whole number.  Before that, numbers like "one," "two," "three," etc., don't contain the letter "A."

